name: FTargetDeviceServicePong
doc: Implements a message that is sent in response to target device service discovery messages.

Connected: Holds a flag indicating whether the device is currently connected.
Authorized: Holds a flag indicating whether the device is authorized.
HostName: Holds the name of the host computer that the device is attached to.
HostUser: Holds the name of the user under which the host computer is running.
Make: Holds the make of the device, i.e. Microsoft or Sony.
Model: Holds the model of the device.
Name: FString
Holds the human readable name of the device, i.e "Bob's XBox'.
DeviceUser: Holds the name of the user that we log in to remote device as, i.e "root".
DeviceUserPassword: Holds the password of the user that we log in to remote device as, i.e "12345".
Shared: Holds a flag indicating whether this device is shared with other users on the network.
SupportsMultiLaunch: Holds a flag indicating whether the device supports running multiple application instances in parallel.
SupportsPowerOff: Holds a flag indicating whether the device can be powered off.
SupportsPowerOn: Holds a flag indicating whether the device can be powered on.
SupportsReboot: Holds a flag indicating whether the device can be rebooted.
SupportsVariants: Holds a flag indicating whether the device's target platform supports variants.
DefaultVariant: Holds the variant name of the default device.
Variants: List of the Flavors this service supports
AllDevicesName: Holds the name of "All devices" proxy.
AllDevicesDefaultVariant: Holds the default variant name of "All devices" proxy.
